Smart Contract Developer Jobs in India

Overview
A Smart Contract Developer in India works on blockchain-based applications such as DeFi, NFTs, Web3 platforms, and blockchain protocols, primarily using Solidity and Ethereum-compatible networks.

Job Role: Smart Contract Developer
Key Responsibilities:

Design, write, test, and deploy smart contracts
Develop ERC-20, ERC-721, and ERC-1155 token standards
Optimize gas usage and contract performance
Identify and fix security vulnerabilities
Integrate smart contracts with Web3 frontends and backend systems

Required Skills: 

Solidity (mandatory)
Ethereum, Polygon, BNB Chain
Hardhat, Truffle, or Foundry
JavaScript / TypeScript
Ethers.js or Web3.js
Smart contract security fundamentals
Git and GitHub

Tier 1: Fresher / Entry-Level Smart Contract Jobs (India)

Best suited for students, freshers, and junior developers.

Companies list:

Polygon Labs, CoinDCX, CoinSwitch, ZebPay, WazirX, Antier Solutions
LeewayHertz, HashCash Consultants, SoluLab, Blockchain App Factory
Nadcab Labs

Common Roles: 
Junior Smart Contract Developer
Blockchain Developer (Trainee)
Web3 Developer Intern


Tier 2: Mid-Level Smart Contract Jobs (India / Remote)

Suitable for developers with 1–3 years of experience or strong project portfolios.

Companies: 
Consensys India, Instadapp, Biconomy, Router Protocol, Push Protocol (EPNS),
Mudrex, Polygon Technology, Chainlink Labs (Remote – India), Alchemy (Remote – India)

Common Roles:
Smart Contract Developer
Web3 Engineer
Blockchain Engineer

Tier 3: Advanced / Protocol-Level Smart Contract Jobs

High-level roles requiring deep blockchain knowledge and security expertise.

Companies:
Polygon Protocol Team, Shardeum, 5ire, Zebec Protocol,Ethereum Foundation (Remote)
Gelato Network (India Team), Instadapp (Core Team)
Common Roles:
Protocol Engineer
Senior Blockchain Engineer
Smart Contract Auditor

Tier 4: Smart Contract Auditing & Security Companies (India)

Focused on blockchain security and auditing roles.

Companies:
QuillAudits, CredShields, TAC Security, Zokyo, BlockSec India

Common Roles:

Smart Contract Auditor
Blockchain Security Engineer

How to Get Hired Faster in India

1. Build 3–5 real-world smart contract projects
2. Deploy contracts on Polygon or Ethereum testnets
3. Maintain an active GitHub portfolio
4. Participate in ETHIndia and Polygon hackathons
5. Network actively on LinkedIn, Discord, and Web3 communities


